on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%202019%2C%20Senffner%20owned%20a%20small%20business%20focused%20on%20learning%20and%20development%2C%20and%20she%20said%20she%20was%20able%20to%20earn%20sufficient%20income%20through%20her%20business%20to%20afford%20her%20everyday%20expenses%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20some.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20the%20pandemic%20hit%2C%20she%20was%20forced%20to%20shut%20down%20her%20business%2C%20and%20she%20could%20not%20find%20any%20source%20of%20income%20for%20about%20two%20years.%20This%20forced%20her%20to%20take%20money%20out%20of%20her%20401(k)%20and%20savings%20account%20because%20her%20husband's%20salary%20was%20not%20big%20enough%20to%20fully%20support%20both%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20according%20to%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Senffner%20has%20no%20money%20in%20savings%20%E2%80%94%20and%20she%20doesn't%20see%20her%20situation%20improving%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-gen-z-millennials-uncertainty-fears-pensions-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eby%20the%20time%20she's%20set%20to%20retire%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20just%20under%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20between%20contract%20jobs%2C%20and%20I%20have%20no%20savings.%20I%20was%20somebody%20who%20did%20really%20well%2C%20and%20it's%20very%20disheartening%20because%20I%20have%20no%20idea%20what's%20going%20to%20happen%20with%20retirement%2C%26quot%3B%20Senffner%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BMy%20husband%20and%20I%20are%20both%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20from%20retirement%20age%2C%20but%20I%20think%20I'll%20probably%20need%20to%20work%20until%20I%20die%20because%20there's%20no%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221106%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Diane%20Senffner%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66296c500dfb1341e9fed4ac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221771%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDiane%20Senffner%20is%20worried%20she'll%20never%20be%20able%20to%20retire.%3Cp%3EDiane%20Senffner%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESenffner%20is%20part%20of%20a%20cohort%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-retirement-of-peak-boomers-could-affect-economy-social-security-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eknown%20as%20%26quot%3Bpeak%20boomers%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20boomers%20born%20between%201959%20and%201964%20who%20will%20start%20turning%2065%20this%20year.%20According%20to%20a%20recent%20report%20from%20the%20Alliance%20for%20Lifetime%20Income's%20Retirement%20Income%20Institute%2C%20this%20group%20encompasses%20over%2030%20million%20boomers%2C%20marking%20the%20%26quot%3Blargest%20and%20final%20cohort%26quot%3B%20of%20that%20generation%20entering%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20found%20that%2052.5%25%20of%20peak%20boomers%20have%20%24250%2C000%20or%20less%20in%20assets%2C%20forcing%20them%20to%20deplete%20their%20savings%20and%20rely%20on%20Social%20Security%20benefits%20to%20stay%20afloat%20in%20retirement.%20But%20Senffner%20said%20that%20the%20around%20%241%2C800%20she%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-budget-proposal-child-tax-credit-social-security-taxing-rich-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eget%20from%20Social%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20month%20would%20not%20cover%20her%20rent%2C%20groceries%2C%20and%20prescriptions%2C%20likely%20requiring%20her%20to%20continue%20working%20to%20supplement%20the%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20simple%20math%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20talking%20about%20retiring%2C%20needing%20about%20%244%2C000%20a%20month%2C%20at%20least%2C%20just%20to%20cover%20expenses.%20Just%20Social%20Security%20isn't%20going%20to%20cover%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20issue%20many%20older%20Americans%20are%20grappling%20with.%20According%20to%20the%20Census%20Bureau's%20Current%20Population%20Survey%2C%20just%20over%20half%20of%20Americans%20over%2065%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-crisis-social-security-poverty-older-americans-savings-inequality-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20incomes%20of%20%2430%2C000%20or%20less%20a%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20existing%20only%20on%20Social%20Security%20likely%20won't%20cut%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20with%20the%20Social%20Security%20fund%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ssa.gov%2Fpolicy%2Fdocs%2Fssb%2Fv70n3%2Fv70n3p111.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eset%20to%20dry%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20late%202030s%20%E2%80%94%20unless%20lawmakers%20intervene%20%E2%80%94%20Senffner%20is%20%26quot%3Bincredibly%20scared%26quot%3B%20about%20her%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20expenses%20are%20enormous%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BTo%20be%20a%20contractor%2C%20I%20have%20to%20have%20internet.%20I%20have%20to%20have%20a%20cell%20phone.%20I%20have%20to%20have%20an%20office%2C%20which%20I%20can%20still%20deduct%20from%20my%20taxes%2C%20but%20in%20the%20immediate%2C%20I%20have%20to%20pay%20for%20those%20things.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'Everybody%20my%20age%20is%20a%20little%20worried%20right%20now'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Senffner%20has%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20the%20workforce%2C%20she%20hasn't%20been%20able%20to%20land%20a%20full-time%20job%20despite%20filling%20out%20dozens%20of%20job%20applications.%20The%20only%20full-time%20jobs%20she's%20seen%20have%20tended%20to%20be%20more%20physically%20demanding%2C%20like%20working%20at%20a%20grocery%20store%2C%20which%20she's%20unable%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20that%20many%20of%20her%20peers%20are%20struggling%20with%20the%20same%20dilemma%20%E2%80%94%20they%20either%20cannot%20find%20work%20in%20fields%20they're%20qualified%20for%2C%20or%20they%20have%20to%20work%20at%20an%20entry-level%20job%20with%20a%20low%20wage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20only%20people%20that%20are%20hiring%20older%20people%20now%20are%20places%20like%20Home%20Depot%20and%20Walmart%2C%26quot%3B%20Senffner%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20say%20to%20my%20friends%20as%20a%20cautionary%20tale%2C%20if%20you%20are%20my%20age%20and%20you%20have%20a%20job%2C%20you%20better%20stay%20with%20it%2C%20because%20nobody%20is%20hiring%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20October%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aarp.org%2Fwork%2Fcareers%2Folder-workers-entry-level-jobs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20AARP%2C%20%26quot%3Bage%20discrimination%20often%20prevents%20older%20adults%20from%20landing%20jobs%20at%20the%20same%20level%20as%20their%20recent%20employment%20or%20higher.%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20the%20AARP%20referenced%20a%20September%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.prweb.com%2Freleases%2Fsurge-in-us-seniors-applying-for-entry-level-positions-301940065.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20The%20Harris%20Poll%20that%20found%20that%2060%25%20of%20hiring%20managers%20prefer%20hiring%20older%20candidates%20over%20younger%20ones%20for%20entry-level%20positions%20because%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20reliable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20with%20the%20low%20wages%20and%20sometimes%20physical%20demands%20of%20entry-level%20work%2C%20it's%20often%20not%20an%20option%20for%20those%20close%20to%20retirement.%20AARP%20recently%20released%20the%20results%20of%20a%20January%20survey%20that%20found%20that%20one%20in%20five%20older%20adults%20do%20not%20have%20any%20retirement%20savings%2C%20and%20over%20half%20of%20them%20don't%20think%20they'll%20have%20enough%20money%20to%20get%20them%20through%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20my%20age%20is%20a%20little%20worried%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Senffner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20know%20so%20many%20people%20my%20age%20that%20just%20don't%20know%20what%20they're%20going%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20continued