a%20rule%20of%20Information%20Technology%20(Intermediary%20Guidelines%20and%20Digital%20Media%20Ethics%20Code)%20Rules%2C%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rule%20in%20question%2C%20Rule%204(2)%2C%20states%20that%20social%20media%20companies%20engaged%20in%20providing%20messaging%20services%20should%20reveal%20who%20sent%20a%20message%20if%20there%20is%20an%20order%20to%20do%20so%20by%20a%20court%20or%20a%20competent%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20significant%20social%20media%20intermediary%20providing%20services%20primarily%20in%20the%20nature%20of%20messaging%20shall%20enable%20the%20identification%20of%20the%20first%20originator%20of%20the%20information%20on%20its%20computer%20resource%20as%20may%20be%20required%20by%20a%20judicial%20order%20passed%20by%20a%20court%20of%20competent%20jurisdiction%20or%20an%20order%20passed%20under%20section%2069%20by%20the%20Competent%20Authority%20as%20per%20the%20Information%20Technology%20(Procedure%20and%20Safeguards%20for%20interception%2C%20monitoring%20and%20decryption%20of%20information)%20Rules%2C%202009%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20rule%20states.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20comes%20with%20a%20caveat%20that%20the%20information%20will%20only%20be%20sought%20for%20offences%20related%20to%20national%20security%2C%20public%20order%2C%20or%20those%20related%20to%20rape%2C%20sexually%20explicit%20material%20or%20child%20sexual%20abuse%20material%2C%20which%20provide%20for%20a%20minimum%20jail%20term%20of%20five%20years.%20It%20also%20states%20that%20an%20order%20of%20this%20nature%20will%20not%20be%20passed%20if%20less%20intrusive%20means%20can%20identify%20the%20originator%20of%20the%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20WhatsApp%20Said%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20petition%2C%20WhatsApp%20has%20sought%20that%20the%20rule%20be%20declared%20unconstitutional%20and%20that%20no%20criminal%20liability%20should%20accrue%20to%20it%20for%20non-compliance.%20The%20traceability%20requirement%2C%20the%20petition%20said%2C%20would%20force%20the%20company%20to%20break%20end-to-end%20encryption%20and%20violate%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20to%20privacy%20and%20free%20speech%20of%20the%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20users%20who%20use%20WhatsApp's%20platform%20to%20communicate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStressing%20on%20this%20point%20and%20asserting%20that%20the%20rule%20was%20brought%20in%20without%20any%20consultation%2C%20Advocate%20Tejas%20Karia%2C%20appearing%20for%20WhatsApp%2C%20told%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20that%20people%20use%20the%20messaging%20platform%20because%20it%20guarantees%20privacy%20with%20its%20end-to-end%20encryption.%20%26quot%3BAs%20a%20platform%2C%20we%20are%20saying%2C%20if%20we%20are%20told%20to%20break%20encryption%2C%20then%20WhatsApp%20goes%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20bench%20of%20Acting%20Chief%20Justice%20Manmohan%20and%20Justice%20Manmeet%20Pritam%20Singh%20Arora%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Fbreaking-encryption-whatsapp-delhi-high-court-challenge-it-rules%5C%22%3EBar%20and%20Bench%3C%2Fa%3E%20report.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20key%20contention%20was%20that%20the%20rule%20would%20require%20WhatsApp%20to%20store%20millions%20of%20messages%20for%20years.%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20have%20to%20keep%20a%20complete%20chain%20and%20we%20don't%20know%20which%20messages%20will%20be%20asked%20to%20be%20decrypted.%20It%20means%20millions%20and%20millions%20of%20messages%20will%20have%20to%20be%20stored%20for%20a%20number%20of%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20then%20asked%20if%20the%20rule%20was%20in%20place%20anywhere%20else%20in%20the%20world.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%26quot%3BHave%20these%20matters%20been%20taken%20up%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world%3F%20You%20have%20never%20been%20asked%20to%20share%20the%20information%20anywhere%20in%20the%20world%3F%20Even%20in%20South%20America%3F%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%2C%20not%20even%20in%20Brazil%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20advocate%20replied.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Balance%20Needed'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20said%20privacy%20rights%20are%20not%20absolute%20and%20%26quot%3Bsomewhere%20balance%20has%20to%20be%20done.%26quot%3B%20This%20was%20after%20the%20Central%20government%20counsel%20said%20the%20rule%20was%20needed%20to%20trace%20the%20originator%20of%20messages%20on%20such%20platforms%20in%20cases%20like%20those%20related%20to%20communal%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20also%20told%20the%20court%20that%20WhatsApp%20and%20Facebook%20monetise%20users'%20information%20and%20are%20not%20legally%20entitled%20to%20claim%20that%20it%20protects%20privacy.%20Efforts%20to%20make%20Facebook%20more%20accountable%20are%20underway%20in%20various%20countries%2C%20it%20pointed%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20had%20also%20said%20earlier%20that%20if%20there%20is%20no%20way%20to%20find%20the%20originator%20of%20messages%20without%20breaking%20encryption%2C%20then%20WhatsApp%20should%20come%20up%20with%20some%20other%20mechanism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20will%20now%20hear%20the%20cases%20on%20August%2014.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714119480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-08%2Fdf80j81o_whatsapp_295x200_09_August_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplained-why-whatsapp-has-warned-of-platforms-end-in-india-5527370%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22WhatsApp's%20big%20statement%20in%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20that%20breaking%20message%20encryption%20would%20be%20the%20end%20of%20the%20platform%20in%20India%20has%20sparked%20a%20debate%20on%20the%20balance%20between%20right%20to%20privacy%20and%20the%20government's%20need%20to%20ensure%20national%20security.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fexplained-wh